Subject: RE: [VB] Fuel sender question...

Here is what I know so far:
1)The gauge does not peg when the sender wire is disconnected from the
sender. So no short in the wires to the sender.
2) I tested the resistance of the sender and I get 70 at full and about
15 at empty so I think the sender is good.
3)2 different gauges with same problem so I don't think he gauge is at
fault.

All I can think is that the ground on the sender was bad. Im not sure
how that would cause it to peg. I will try to replace that tomorrow. On
the plus side, once this is fixed the whole rewiring project should be
done! Whoohoo!
TJ

